  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_type_S_connected_Helly_and_highs_le_K",
      "statement": "(1) Prove Type S multipads are always intersection-connected (toys: always 1 component), and/or Helly (common intersection) often enough to apply maximal-common packing M_pad\u226416 deployed.\n(2) Prove |H_A_SP| \u2264 2176 (or constructive \u03ba) at deployed scale.\nMaximal-common case already gives M_pad\u226416 (near pack_ceil=17).",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "common_bound": {
      "deployed_bound": 846160,
      "name": "multipad_global_common_intersection_bound",
      "proof": [
        "Pick C\u2260C' in Cores. v27: deg(\u039b_C\u2212\u039b_{C'}) \u2264 free_core\u22121 and every common root of C,C' is a root of \u0394.",
        "Global common I \u2286 C\u2229C' \u2286 roots of \u0394 \u21d2 |I| \u2264 deg(\u0394) \u2264 free_core\u22121 unless \u0394\u22610, which would force C=C'."
      ],
      "statement": "For any multipad core set Cores with |Cores|\u22652, |\u22c2_{C\u2208Cores} C| \u2264 free_core \u2212 1.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "high_count": {
      "deployed_targets": {
        "K_Mpad1": 2176,
        "K_Mpad2": 1088
      },
      "name": "active_high_counting_bounds",
      "proof": [
        "Each active high has \u22651 CS ordered pair (actually \u22652: (U,V) and (V,U) when both directions appear; at least one direction).",
        "Map high \u21a6 one of its ordered pairs is injective into the set of side pairs counted by N_side / N_ord.",
        "v30 high-tag budget."
      ],
      "statement": "Let H_A_SP be the set of free-1 highs that appear in at least one A_SP free-1 CS ordered pair. Then |H_A_SP| \u2264 N_side \u2264 N_ord. Fiber-local: for each z, |H_A_SP(z)| \u2264 N_ord(z). Payment needs |H_A_SP| \u2264 2176 (M_pad\u22641 path) or \u2264 1088 (M_pad\u22642 half-budget path) for (\u03ba,\u03b9,\u03b4) to fit e\u00b7p.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "maximal_pack": {
      "deployed": {
        "I_size": 846160,
        "M_pad_bound": 16,
        "equals_A_over_e_floor": true,
        "g_reduced": 1116048,
        "m_reduced": 67472
      },
      "name": "maximal_common_intersection_packing",
      "proof": [
        "All pairs share I of size free_core\u22121. For any C\u2260C', \u0394 vanishes on I with deg(\u0394)\u2264 free_core\u22121 \u21d2 \u0394 = \u03b1 \u220f_{r\u2208I}(X\u2212r), \u03b1\u22600.",
        "Hence reduced monics differ by a nonzero constant: free-1 CS of size m_c\u2212|I| (v23/v25 style).",
        "v25 packing: free-1 family pairwise disjoint; ground set size n\u22122e\u2212|I| (avoid U,V and I).",
        "Deployed arithmetic: free_core\u22121 = j\u22122w\u22122 = m_c\u2212w\u22121, m_c\u2212(free_core\u22121) = w+1 = e; n\u22122e\u2212(free_core\u22121) = n\u2212e\u2212(j\u2212w\u22121) ... check: free_core\u22121 = j\u22122w\u22122 = (n\u2212A)\u22122(t\u22121)\u22122 = n\u2212A\u22122t; numerically n\u22122e\u2212(free_core\u22121) = A."
      ],
      "statement": "If a multipad core set has global common intersection I with |I| = free_core \u2212 1, then the reduced cores C\\I are free-1 CS of size m_c\u2212|I|, pairwise disjoint on D\\(U\u222aV\u222aI), hence M_pad \u2264 \u230a(n\u22122e\u2212|I|)/(m_c\u2212|I|)\u230b. Deployed: |I|=free_core\u22121 \u21d2 m_c\u2212|I|=e=67472, n\u22122e\u2212|I|=A=1116048, M_pad \u2264 \u230aA/e\u230b = 16.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "mpad2": {
      "name": "mpad_2_type_S_is_connected_edge",
      "proof": [
        "M_pad=2 \u21d2 one pair of cores. Type S \u21d2 t\u22652 \u21d2 they share a root.",
        "v27: |C\u2229C'| \u2264 free_core\u22121."
      ],
      "statement": "Any Type S multipad with M_pad=2 consists of a single intersecting pair: the intersection graph is one edge, and 1 \u2264 |C\u2229C'| \u2264 free_core\u22121.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
